    "spell": {
        "name": "Reflective Scales",
        "type": "stat_block_section",
        "text": "You grow a set of colored, glowing scales or scaled armor that stores energy before releasing it in a final burst. When you cast this spell, choose acid, cold, fire, electricity, or poison damage. You gain resistance 5 against that type of damage. The scales\u2019 color depends on the damage type you chose, such as red or orange for fire damage.  \n  \nThe scales store up energy as they protect you. Keep track of how much damage the scales have prevented. As a 2-action activity that has the concentrate and manipulate traits, you can explode your scales outward in a 20-foot emanation, dealing 1d6 damage of the chosen type to all creatures in the area for every 10 damage the scales have prevented, to a maximum of 10d6 damage (after preventing 100 damage). Each creature in the area must attempt a basic Reflex save. Once you do so, the spell ends.",
        "subtype": "spell",
        "spell_type": "spell",
        "rank": 4,
        "traits": [
            {
